>>>>>>> An in-depth information book on diabetes care, insulin, food, day-to-
day issues and complications specific to Type 1 diabetes.
>>>>>>> An in-depth guide for people newly diagnosed with Type 2 diabetes,
covering treatment, healthcare, healthy living, available support and personal
>>>>>>> This guide helps you to understand gestational diabetes, gives
practical tips on healthy eating and physical activity, and explains the care
and treatment you'll receive to help you have a healthy pregnancy and labour.
>>>>>>> The "Your child and diabetes" guide covers diabetes care, food, day-
to-day issues and support and guidance specific to families of a child with
>>>>>>> Sets out clearly what happens when you have the condition.
>>>>>>> This is an introduction to both Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes, as well as
details of where to find more information and support. Being told you have
diabetes can be overwhelming – this leaflet is designed to give basic
information right now, and clear advice on what to do next.
>>>>>>> Our free, online diabetes education module giving a user personalised
content based on their diabetes type, treatments and demographic
>>>>>>> To help you and your patients with the transition from the percentage
system you were used to, we have developed a converter.
>>>>>>> Information prescriptions are designed to give people with diabetes
the information they need to understand and improve on their health targets.
>>>>>>> There are a range of tests which will need to be done for people with
diabetes to monitor their health. Diabetes UK provides a rang of information
about these various tests. The Balance Guide to Glucose testing acknowledges
that diabetes can be a very complicated condition to live with, and only by
testing and knowing how to respond to the results can you live a healthy life.
The supplement includes blood glucose testing at home to testing at clinics
and why, when and the benefit of testing.
